	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_CSAGREEN">
			<Text>Green</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_CSAGREEN_HELP">
			<Text>Replaced with a randomly chosen Confederate General (promotion) after the unit completes its first round of combat.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_CSAREBELYELL">
			<Text>Rebel Yell!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_CSAREBELYELL_HELP">
			<Text>Unit may force enemy units to retreat!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_AWRIGHT_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]Unit may embark, and has extra defensive strength while doing so.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Part of a rare Confederate amphibious operation to reinforce Roanoke Island, North Carolina to defend it from Union assault.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_BHUGER_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_NEGATIVE_TEXT]-20% [ICON_STRENGTH] When defending.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Evacuated Norfolk early in the Peninsula Campaign, forcing the Confederates to scuttle the ironclad CSS Virginia.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_RRODES_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]Combat is more likely to create Great Generals.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Commanded the first wave of "Stonewall" Jackson's flank attack at Chancellorsville, helping create the legend of that general.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_STONEWALL_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]Flanking Bonus increased by 100%.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Nicknamed "Stonewall" at 1st Bull Run, he led decisive flanking maneuvers during the 2nd Bull Run and Chancellorsville campaigns, and is considered among the most gifted generals in American history.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_WMAHONE_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]20% stronger while fighting in the capital; bonus falls off as the unit gets further away.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]The hero of the Battle of the Crater, an ill-fated Union attempt to tunnel under the siege lines defending Petersburg.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_AJOHNSTON">
			<Text>Albert Sidney Johnston</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_AJOHNSTON_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]Heals fully from pillaging tiles.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Undersupplied on men and ammunition, conducted many raids on Union camps in Kentucky to make it appear as though he had many more troops than in reality. So unnerved by this, General William Sherman overestimated the Confederate forces, and was relieved of command.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_BADMILTIA">
			<Text>Rebel Militia</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_BADMILTIA_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_NEGATIVE_TEXT]-20% [ICON_STRENGTH] outside of friendly territory.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]This unit is a disorganized local force with no prominent leaders, and with little knowledge of lands other than their own.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_BBRAGG">
			<Text>Braxton Bragg</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_BBRAGG_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_NEGATIVE_TEXT]-20% [ICON_STRENGTH] combat penalty. Unit has a 75% chance to withdraw if attacked by an enemy.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Considered among the worst of Civil War leaders, his problems were legendary on the battlefield. Failing to properly communicate with his generals, he suffered a number of blunders, including following a 6-month-old order to retreat to Chattanooga when he discovered that the enemy was advancing on his position. When a brigade of Union men attacked that city, his army went into full retreat.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_NFORREST">
			<Text>Nathan Forrest</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_NFORREST_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]May capture defeated enemies.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]With a force of 3,500 men, forced an 8,500-man Union force into retreat at the battle of Brice's Crossroads, and captured 16 artillery pieces, 176 wagons, and 1,500 stands of small arms.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_JSTUART">
			<Text>Jeb Stuart</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_JSTUART_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]Ignores enemy zone of control.[ENDCOLOR][NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Sent to ride around the Army of the Potomac during the Peninsular campaign in Virginia, after being sent on a reconnaissance of Union positions by Robert E. Lee. Four days later, Stuart had circled the entire Yankee force, 105,000 strong, and provided Lee with crucial information.</Text>
		</Row>
